    "Sieve 2SLS with learned spectral featuresIn the previous section, we showed that spectral features minimize the sieve measure of ill-posedness and lead to fast generalization rates when the structural function h 0 aligns well with the top eigenspaces of the conditional expectation operator T. This motivates learning such features directly from data, especially in the case where the conditional distribution of X given Z is informative (i.e., the instrument is strong) and the alignment with the spectrum of T is favorable.",
    "We now demonstrate that the contrastive learning approach of [36] can be equivalently seen as explicitly targeting the leading eigenspaces of T. Consider the following objective:L d (φ, ψ).",
